Ros Agro First-Half Sugar Production Expands 35%, Pork Drops 10%

-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 
2011-07-27T12:01:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-27/ros-agro-first-half-sugar-production-expands-35-pork-drops-10-.html
Ros Agro Plc, a Russian agriculture
holding company, boosted sugar output by 35 percent, while
cutting pork production 10 percent after a drought.  The producer, known as Rusagro, produced 529,000 metric
tons of sugar, up from 392,000 tons, it said in a  statement  on
its website. Pork output fell to 28,000 tons after the drought
last year that affected pigsâ€™ feeding and growth, the company
said. Animal feed rose 65 percent to 33,000 tons, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
